WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.940 --> 00:00:06.230
Inarizaki                                                                                                        Karasuno

2
00:00:06.230 --> 00:00:10.480
Inarizaki seems to be adding 
their captain, Kita Shinsuke, back in.

3
00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:11.940
Are they strengthening their defense?

4
00:00:12.330 --> 00:00:14.160
I believe so.

5
00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:19.960
Inarizaki seems stronger, defensively 
and mentally, when he's on the court.

6
00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:24.520
I probably shouldn't be the 
one to bring this up, but...

7
00:00:25.040 --> 00:00:26.140
What?

8
00:00:26.140 --> 00:00:30.270
Wouldn't putting me back in 
right now be passively defensive?

9
00:00:30.270 --> 00:00:34.480
Huh? Wha?! This is my best offensive attack!

10
00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:37.010
The Miyas are totally on point today.

11
00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:39.800
So if I'm putting you in, it means 
that the last thing they should do

12
00:00:39.800 --> 00:00:41.210
is step on the brakes.

13
00:00:43.430 --> 00:00:48.690
We Don't Need the Memories

14
00:00:43.430 --> 00:00:48.690
Inarizaki High School Volleyball Club

15
00:00:45.010 --> 00:00:48.300
To be honest, I don't like that motto.

16
00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:51.840
It's not like the path 
is only in front of us.

17
00:00:51.840 --> 00:00:53.900
Focusing and being rash
 are two different things.

18
00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:57.820
I don't understand guys like them at all.

19
00:00:58.450 --> 00:00:59.260
But...

20
00:01:00.010 --> 00:01:02.840
Watching them does make my heart stir.

21
00:01:03.990 --> 00:01:07.120
I'm not a player that can 
change the flow of things,

22
00:01:07.120 --> 00:01:09.950
I'm pretty sure we could've 
pulled that off.

23
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:13.130
but I feel like I need to watch the backs 
of these guys who just keep running ahead.

24
00:01:09.950 --> 00:01:13.660
Let it go. You messed that 
up when we were kids.

25
00:01:13.660 --> 00:01:15.090
Pretty sure I can do it now.

26
00:01:16.880 --> 00:01:21.050
You're probably in the same boat.

27
00:01:36.990 --> 00:01:43.990
Haikyu

28
00:02:54.190 --> 00:02:57.230
Episode 23: The Birth of the Serene King

29
00:02:58.190 --> 00:02:59.260
Got it!

30
00:02:59.260 --> 00:03:00.610
One more! One more!

31
00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:08.090
Nice kill, Rintaro!

32
00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:09.000
We Don't Need the Memories

33
00:03:08.090 --> 00:03:11.430
Nice kill, Rintaro! Jump, jump, Rintaro!

34
00:03:10.560 --> 00:03:12.620
Looks like you don't have enough stamina.

35
00:03:16.450 --> 00:03:17.830
Probably.

36
00:03:25.820 --> 00:03:26.570
It's coming back.

37
00:03:26.570 --> 00:03:27.680
Free ball!

38
00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:28.730
Got it!

39
00:03:29.610 --> 00:03:31.610
Synchronized attack!

40
00:03:36.790 --> 00:03:37.910
We're not syncing.

41
00:03:41.960 --> 00:03:43.200
The quick didn't go through.

42
00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:45.660
That mistake's gotta hurt for Karasuno.

43
00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:46.450
Inarizaki                                                                   Karasuno

44
00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:49.050
Damn it! It was too high.

45
00:03:49.050 --> 00:03:49.740
Sorry—

46
00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:51.220
Could you not apologize?

47
00:03:52.550 --> 00:03:54.470
I just didn't jump high enough.

48
00:03:56.920 --> 00:03:59.460
Always jumping with the intention 
of hitting the ball over...

49
00:04:00.230 --> 00:04:02.760
Always making sure there's a good 
distance for the approach...

50
00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:08.030
Hinata always does this?
 Actually, even more than this?

51
00:04:08.890 --> 00:04:10.140
Shut up.

52
00:04:10.460 --> 00:04:13.270
I estimated wrong. It's my mistake.

53
00:04:13.780 --> 00:04:16.840
It's amazing how much you don't 
seem like you mean any of that.

54
00:04:18.270 --> 00:04:20.270
So can you do this?

55
00:04:20.270 --> 00:04:21.820
Of course.

56
00:04:23.190 --> 00:04:24.640
We're gonna get the next one!

57
00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:25.820
Yeah!

58
00:04:27.540 --> 00:04:30.590
I'm pretty sure you could've 
followed up on that last one.

59
00:04:30.590 --> 00:04:32.200
Let's nail this one!

60
00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:38.540
Serving for Karasuno is Azumane Asahi.

61
00:04:38.540 --> 00:04:40.420
He's definitely one of their 
best servers,

62
00:04:40.420 --> 00:04:43.850
but I'd say he's only been nailing 
about half of his serves today.

63
00:04:43.850 --> 00:04:45.880
Things are still up in the air.

64
00:04:46.370 --> 00:04:50.230
Well, their opponents do have the lead 
in the last part of the final set.

65
00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:53.600
I'm pretty sure he's feeling even
 more pressure than he's used to.

66
00:04:56.610 --> 00:04:58.180
One hundred percent...

67
00:04:59.350 --> 00:05:01.480
Bring it!

68
00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:19.450
He did it! Azumane Asahi, 
showing us why he's the ace!

69
00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:21.390
That's a no-touch ace!

70
00:05:21.390 --> 00:05:27.030
Nice, nice, Asahi! Push it, push it, 
Asahi! One more time!

71
00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:27.580
Good job, samurai boy!

72
00:05:27.580 --> 00:05:29.320
Kick-ass serve!

73
00:05:30.020 --> 00:05:31.600
Damn those geezers!

74
00:05:32.280 --> 00:05:34.090
The Karasuno samurai...

75
00:05:34.090 --> 00:05:36.910
He probably starts off at around 
80 percent, and then gradually

76
00:05:36.910 --> 00:05:39.230
gets more and more powerful 
throughout the match,

77
00:05:39.230 --> 00:05:43.000
letting loose his full power 
in the final part of the final set.

78
00:05:43.940 --> 00:05:45.500
Man, I'm hungry, Samu!

79
00:05:45.500 --> 00:05:47.530
Same here, Tsumu.

80
00:05:47.800 --> 00:05:50.530
One more time!

81
00:05:49.820 --> 00:05:51.030
Shinsuke!

82
00:05:52.460 --> 00:05:54.040
Nice receive!

83
00:05:54.350 --> 00:05:57.650
The captain, Kita, bumped that 
powerful serve up beautifully.

84
00:05:57.650 --> 00:06:00.290
I have no idea if I could've 
gotten that, damn it.

85
00:06:00.290 --> 00:06:02.340
Who's Miya Atsumu going to use?

86
00:06:04.360 --> 00:06:05.880
Please come together...

87
00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:07.380
for a powerful two-man block!

88
00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:10.140
Yes!

89
00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:10.970
Cover!

90
00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:11.850
Got it!

91
00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:16.100
Nice receive!

92
00:06:16.100 --> 00:06:18.700
Man, what the hell?

93
00:06:18.700 --> 00:06:20.100
This is definitely it!

94
00:06:20.100 --> 00:06:22.480
Wait, he's in the back 
row right now, isn't he?

95
00:06:23.730 --> 00:06:25.230
Right now...

96
00:06:25.230 --> 00:06:29.240
Every single time, "now" is 
the best chance we've got!

97
00:06:31.220 --> 00:06:32.370
Twins' quick...

98
00:06:32.810 --> 00:06:34.160
...minus tempo...

99
00:06:34.590 --> 00:06:35.720
reverse!

100
00:06:45.670 --> 00:06:47.740
Nice follow-through!

101
00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:51.790
I don't want to lose...

102
00:06:51.790 --> 00:06:53.500
We won't lose.

103
00:06:53.500 --> 00:06:55.180
We're not going to stop yet.

104
00:06:55.180 --> 00:06:59.060
Now, just watch me get the next one!

105
00:07:02.090 --> 00:07:08.030
"I don't want to lose." "We have to win."
 How could we be so naïve?

106
00:07:08.710 --> 00:07:12.740
Victory and defeat... Those are just results!

107
00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:14.950
Our concept doesn't change.

108
00:07:15.490 --> 00:07:17.160
This point right now...

109
00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:19.180
...is what we're fighting for.

110
00:07:21.790 --> 00:07:23.590
Synchronized attack!

111
00:07:24.640 --> 00:07:26.510
During their match with Shiratorizawa,

112
00:07:26.510 --> 00:07:28.880
they didn't attack from 
the back a single time.

113
00:07:28.880 --> 00:07:32.950
It just happened once today as a 
surprise attack to cut off Atsumu's serves.

114
00:07:33.640 --> 00:07:38.940
What's the point in doing an attack when 
you're abandoning your position as backup?

115
00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:43.440
I'm not here to protect my teammates.

116
00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:46.650
Each and every one of us 
is here to score!

117
00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:59.240
We Don't Need the Memories

118
00:08:05.880 --> 00:08:11.380
Inarizaki                                                                   Karasuno

119
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:09.100
Yeah!

120
00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:11.380
Karasuno managed to grab hold of 
the distant Inarizaki from behind!

121
00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:25.120
Yeah!

122
00:08:25.120 --> 00:08:28.360
The goddess of victory turns
 her eyes toward Karasuno!

123
00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:30.320
Nice, nice, Kei! Push it, push it,
 Kei! One more time!

124
00:08:28.360 --> 00:08:30.320
Karasuno

125
00:08:28.900 --> 00:08:30.320
Karasuno takes the lead!

126
00:08:30.670 --> 00:08:36.030
Things seemed pretty grim after they 
couldn't score after Hinata-kun's save.

127
00:08:36.660 --> 00:08:38.720
Ever since that time out,

128
00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:41.450
It seems like Karasuno is over
 whatever was dragging them down.

129
00:08:43.210 --> 00:08:44.410
Damn, that was high.

130
00:08:44.410 --> 00:08:46.920
Inarizaki's not wasting
 any time catching back up.

131
00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:55.060
I think these eight seconds are my 
second favorite, after chow time.

132
00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:00.010
Cover!

133
00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:01.640
Kageyama, get the last!

134
00:09:03.930 --> 00:09:05.480
He definitely went after their setter.

135
00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:06.140
Osamu!

136
00:09:06.140 --> 00:09:08.410
Hey, it's what they did earlier.

137
00:09:08.410 --> 00:09:14.110
Nah... I can't imagine they'd try that 
unreliable quick again so soon.

138
00:09:14.840 --> 00:09:17.220
They're definitely going to do it.

139
00:09:18.250 --> 00:09:20.700
You think so, too, don't you?

140
00:09:25.180 --> 00:09:27.530
One and a half blockers!

141
00:09:30.630 --> 00:09:34.090
Inarizaki                                                                 Karasuno

142
00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:34.090
Inarizaki High takes the lead back again!

143
00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:36.520
One more!

144
00:09:36.520 --> 00:09:37.300
Nice kill!

145
00:09:37.580 --> 00:09:39.210
Not bad, Samu!

146
00:09:39.210 --> 00:09:39.900
Right?!

147
00:09:39.900 --> 00:09:40.730
Yeah!

148
00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:43.040
Looks like the Karasuno 
blockers were distracted

149
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:44.720
by Atsumu-kun on the right for a bit.

150
00:09:44.720 --> 00:09:45.730
I see.

151
00:09:45.730 --> 00:09:49.590
I'm sure they're exhausted, 
physically as well as mentally.

152
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:53.210
Damn, I want some carbs right now.

153
00:10:00.640 --> 00:10:01.580
Tanaka-san!

154
00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:02.820
Three blockers!

155
00:10:06.010 --> 00:10:07.250
Nice kill!

156
00:10:07.550 --> 00:10:10.330
Yes, yes, yes! Great job!

157
00:10:10.330 --> 00:10:12.250
Nice kill!

158
00:10:13.920 --> 00:10:14.960
Yeah!

159
00:10:14.960 --> 00:10:18.440
Tsukishima and Hinata still 
aren't the best servers,

160
00:10:18.440 --> 00:10:21.920
so they're probably going to give up
 a point during this rotation.

161
00:10:21.920 --> 00:10:25.260
But that being the case,
if they're able to score here...

162
00:10:26.810 --> 00:10:27.610
Aran!

163
00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:28.470
Got it!

164
00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:32.110
Gotta touch it...

165
00:10:32.110 --> 00:10:35.560
Gotta touch it, gotta touch it, 
gotta touch it, gotta touch it...

166
00:10:37.510 --> 00:10:41.070
And no one expected that setter dump!

167
00:10:41.070 --> 00:10:42.530
Hell yeah!

168
00:10:43.480 --> 00:10:46.680
Hey! Snap out of it! 
There's no time for regrets!

169
00:10:48.240 --> 00:10:51.210
Right when Inarizaki's 
Kita moves to the front,

170
00:10:51.210 --> 00:10:53.000
they're returning Ginjima to the court.

171
00:10:52.310 --> 00:10:53.000
Nice serve.

172
00:11:07.720 --> 00:11:09.070
Yes!

173
00:11:09.070 --> 00:11:12.350
From a powerful serve to Ginjima 
slamming it down for the point!

174
00:11:10.240 --> 00:11:12.350
Yeah!

175
00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:16.360
Looks like Inarizaki's 
going for the checkmate!

176
00:11:14.480 --> 00:11:18.530
Inarizaki                                                                                    Karasuno

177
00:11:16.470 --> 00:11:19.450
Nice kill, Hitoshi!

178
00:11:19.450 --> 00:11:24.410
Nice kill, Hitoshi! Push it, push it,
 Hitoshi! One more time!

179
00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:27.680
We're gonna stay calm.

180
00:11:27.680 --> 00:11:28.720
We'll get that point!

181
00:11:28.720 --> 00:11:29.900
Concentrate!

182
00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:32.830
Damn it, you've got this!

183
00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:35.580
It doesn't matter if you're tired!

184
00:11:36.290 --> 00:11:38.670
It doesn't matter how 
strong your opponent is!

185
00:11:39.070 --> 00:11:42.500
Who the hell cares if you're 
already doing your best?

186
00:11:43.490 --> 00:11:45.110
Try harder, damn it!

187
00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:56.820
This is...

188
00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:00.360
Inarizaki                                                        Karasuno

189
00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:00.360
This is crazy. It feels weird.

190
00:12:00.730 --> 00:12:03.540
I think I'm actually on a roll.

191
00:12:03.540 --> 00:12:05.820
I feel like I'm seeing blocks 
better than I usually do.

192
00:12:06.420 --> 00:12:07.780
Maybe that's why...

193
00:12:08.440 --> 00:12:11.880
That's why my instincts are 
telling me not to go any harder.

194
00:12:14.550 --> 00:12:15.850
Kageyama...

195
00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:18.460
I'm gonna swallow my pride 
and ask you to do this.

196
00:12:19.270 --> 00:12:22.420
Cut back on how many sets
 you send my way for a bit.

197
00:12:36.020 --> 00:12:37.400
No.

198
00:12:37.400 --> 00:12:39.360
Inarizaki                                                                                                        Karasuno

199
00:12:42.840 --> 00:12:44.030
Cover!

200
00:12:44.630 --> 00:12:45.950
Tanaka-san!

201
00:12:59.600 --> 00:13:01.030
Kageyama!

202
00:13:05.730 --> 00:13:07.970
Karasuno follows one quick with another!

203
00:13:07.970 --> 00:13:09.520
But Ojiro managed to get the ball up!

204
00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:10.820
Can someone follow through?

205
00:13:11.340 --> 00:13:13.640
They're not gonna be able 
to get a decent attack.

206
00:13:15.810 --> 00:13:17.020
Scary...

207
00:13:20.250 --> 00:13:22.720
Both setters are some of 
the best in the nation!

208
00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:24.900
They're showing off some insane moves!

209
00:13:25.030 --> 00:13:27.740
Inarizaki                                                        Karasuno

210
00:13:27.090 --> 00:13:27.740
No.

211
00:13:30.760 --> 00:13:33.160
We need your attacks, Tanaka-san.

212
00:13:35.620 --> 00:13:36.870
That...

213
00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:40.340
That wasn't him trying to 
make me feel better...

214
00:13:40.900 --> 00:13:41.800
Kageyama!

215
00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:44.880
It's normal not to know 
what others are thinking.

216
00:13:45.570 --> 00:13:50.350
You need to know the current state of 
the game and your teammates' conditions.

217
00:13:50.800 --> 00:13:55.060
Ever since the end of the first set, Tanaka-san
 definitely hasn't been doing bad at all.

218
00:13:55.580 --> 00:13:59.340
He's been staying calm even
 at times he'd usually go crazy.

219
00:13:59.340 --> 00:14:01.300
That insane cut shot he 
pulled off was amazing, too.

220
00:14:02.580 --> 00:14:06.740
But is that really Tanaka-san's best weapon?

221
00:14:07.190 --> 00:14:10.820
Everyone on our team is strong,
as they should be.

222
00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:15.830
No, that's not for me to decide.

223
00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:20.260
After connecting so many insane attacks,

224
00:14:20.710 --> 00:14:26.000
even at the end of this match, with long rallies, 
recovering from messed-up receives...

225
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:29.420
It's not too short, not too long, 
not too close or too far.

226
00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:32.890
A beautiful toss stretches over our side.

227
00:14:33.250 --> 00:14:36.350
Send it further... to the very edge.

228
00:14:36.670 --> 00:14:39.810
I need to give my spikers options!

229
00:14:41.090 --> 00:14:43.770
Ever since that insane cut shot,

230
00:14:44.080 --> 00:14:47.900
it's subtle, but the blockers are 
definitely shifting for a cross.

231
00:14:49.380 --> 00:14:52.780
The other path that Tanaka 
pried open for us...

232
00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:55.610
That wasn't him trying 
to make me feel better...

233
00:14:56.480 --> 00:14:58.620
All of this trust that he's put in me...

234
00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:01.530
I'm going to see it through!

235
00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:14.570
An insanely sharp line shot!

236
00:15:20.520 --> 00:15:24.480
Fly

237
00:15:21.840 --> 00:15:25.620
I can't believe how sharp that line shot was!

238
00:15:24.850 --> 00:15:26.960
Yeah!

239
00:15:26.960 --> 00:15:29.900
Tanaka Ryunosuke makes his 
presence known once again!

240
00:15:30.210 --> 00:15:32.670
That really was an insane straight 
shot right onto the line!

241
00:15:32.670 --> 00:15:35.620
His positioning suggested 
another cross, but...

242
00:15:36.760 --> 00:15:38.580
Nice, Ryu!

243
00:15:50.150 --> 00:15:51.470
Nice toss!

244
00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:53.270
Nice kill.

245
00:15:53.700 --> 00:15:58.470
Where... Where the hell'd Goody Two-Shoes go?

246
00:15:59.410 --> 00:16:02.490
What the hell happened in 
this short amount of time?

247
00:16:06.120 --> 00:16:08.720
Karasuno High School's Tanaka Ryunosuke

248
00:16:09.150 --> 00:16:12.220
just sliced through Inarizaki's 
defense with that shot!

249
00:16:21.720 --> 00:16:22.860
That guy's weird.

250
00:16:22.860 --> 00:16:24.210
Ma-kun, shh!

251
00:16:27.960 --> 00:16:34.970
Haikyu!!

252
00:16:34.970 --> 00:16:41.980
Haikyu!!

253
00:16:41.980 --> 00:16:47.440
Inarizaki                                                                   Karasuno

254
00:16:42.760 --> 00:16:47.440
Karasuno shows no signs of slowing down,
 but Inarizaki's at match point.

255
00:16:47.820 --> 00:16:50.900
A service error or a serve 
that's too easy to receive...

256
00:16:51.280 --> 00:16:53.800
will mean that Karasuno loses.

257
00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:58.950
I know I don't need to guard my head, but...

258
00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:02.580
I still want to protect the back of my head!

259
00:17:10.670 --> 00:17:13.130
Seriously, what the hell's his deal?

260
00:17:15.590 --> 00:17:19.800
Fly

261
00:17:15.900 --> 00:17:19.800
Did you see those nerves of steel?! 
His unbreakable concentration!

262
00:17:19.800 --> 00:17:23.100
An amazing service ace that 
ties them up once again!

263
00:17:23.100 --> 00:17:25.500
Way to go, Kageyama Tobio!

264
00:17:26.210 --> 00:17:27.480
Yes!

265
00:17:27.480 --> 00:17:30.660
This is going beyond amazing to annoying.

266
00:17:34.430 --> 00:17:36.610
Bring it!

267
00:17:42.930 --> 00:17:43.790
Seriously...

268
00:17:44.170 --> 00:17:45.750
His game today...

269
00:17:46.250 --> 00:17:47.320
Up front!

270
00:17:47.320 --> 00:17:49.210
At the very last possible second,

271
00:17:49.210 --> 00:17:51.770
Kageyama seemed to know exactly 
what the receivers were thinking,

272
00:17:51.770 --> 00:17:53.670
and drops the serve up front!

273
00:17:53.670 --> 00:17:55.350
Free ball!

274
00:18:00.230 --> 00:18:05.600
With lightning speed, Karasuno 
gets one right down the middle!

275
00:18:02.380 --> 00:18:04.760
Yeah!

276
00:18:05.600 --> 00:18:08.460
They knew their opponents 
were thrown off their game!

277
00:18:05.600 --> 00:18:13.070
Inarizaki                                                                            Karasuno

278
00:18:08.460 --> 00:18:10.640
What an incredibly fast hit down the middle!

279
00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:13.070
Now Karasuno's nearing checkmate!

280
00:18:26.080 --> 00:18:27.740
Nice receive!

281
00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:29.920
You're only the ace if you 
can attack and defend!

282
00:18:37.570 --> 00:18:40.300
They knew exactly what they were 
doing there! Ginjima scores on the left.

283
00:18:40.770 --> 00:18:43.430
I'm pretty sure they're all exhausted by now,

284
00:18:43.880 --> 00:18:48.390
but they didn't give the blockers even 
the slightest hint. What a beautiful set.

285
00:18:49.570 --> 00:18:52.720
Even though we're at the 
very end of the game,

286
00:18:52.720 --> 00:18:55.720
he's not thrown off at all, 
and he seems to know what they're thinking.

287
00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:57.610
Did you see Atsumu-kun's set?

288
00:18:57.610 --> 00:18:59.560
That guy's definitely a genius...

289
00:18:59.560 --> 00:19:01.530
It's painful playing the 
same position as him.

290
00:19:01.530 --> 00:19:04.280
Kageyama's serves are crazy, too.

291
00:19:04.280 --> 00:19:06.170
Man, I wish I had talent, too.

292
00:19:06.820 --> 00:19:09.860
I don't remember when, but I was asked...

293
00:19:11.010 --> 00:19:13.260
"You're not a starter,"

294
00:19:13.260 --> 00:19:18.090
"so isn't it hard to have such a genius player
 who's younger than you on the same team?"

295
00:19:18.540 --> 00:19:23.590
I'm not sure what qualifies 
as a "genius," but...

296
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:27.290
I understood what they were trying to say.

297
00:19:27.290 --> 00:19:29.530
There happen to be people who think

298
00:19:29.530 --> 00:19:33.520
that someone like Atsumu was just 
born a talented player. But...

299
00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:38.430
Everything I do every day, 
from a scale of one to ten,

300
00:19:38.430 --> 00:19:41.950
guys like Atsumu do on a 
scale of one to twenty.

301
00:19:42.420 --> 00:19:46.330
Or it's a more effective ten,
 or a denser ten.

302
00:19:47.160 --> 00:19:53.400
And sometimes, instead of one to ten,
 they try things from A to Z.

303
00:19:53.890 --> 00:19:57.460
That's what goes through their heads.

304
00:19:58.750 --> 00:20:02.460
Even if they mess up sometimes, 
or they're hated by strangers,

305
00:20:02.460 --> 00:20:07.260
or cast out... even if they completely ignore 
something we'd consider important...

306
00:20:07.880 --> 00:20:10.180
They just have to do it.

307
00:20:10.180 --> 00:20:13.980
Even if they start coughing up blood, 
they're the guys who just wanna keep running.

308
00:20:15.440 --> 00:20:16.440
One touch!

309
00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:21.280
There are plenty of guys in this 
world who we're no match for,

310
00:20:21.280 --> 00:20:24.970
and it's natural to find 
people like that amazing.

311
00:20:25.940 --> 00:20:29.260
I think being able to dive headfirst 
into things is a talent in and of itself,

312
00:20:29.260 --> 00:20:32.120
and it doesn't matter what you call them.

313
00:20:32.920 --> 00:20:35.580
And it's not like genius is an insult...

314
00:20:35.950 --> 00:20:41.210
But if you're thinking they're 
geniuses from the start,

315
00:20:41.530 --> 00:20:44.720
that just means you've lost before 
you even had a match with them.

316
00:20:44.720 --> 00:20:46.260
And it's rude.

317
00:20:47.060 --> 00:20:48.220
Sorry, it's long!

318
00:20:47.300 --> 00:20:49.800
Karasuno manages to get another one!

319
00:20:49.800 --> 00:20:52.420
What a long rally! 
A rally of sheer willpower!

320
00:20:57.620 --> 00:21:00.220
Damn it... Just five more centimeters...

321
00:21:00.220 --> 00:21:01.700
You should be able to reach that!

322
00:21:02.190 --> 00:21:05.070
Jump higher! Reach!

323
00:21:08.440 --> 00:21:09.460
Damn it!

324
00:21:17.260 --> 00:21:18.540
His foot!

325
00:21:18.850 --> 00:21:22.190
Hinata Shoyo shows incredible 
balance and skill!

326
00:21:21.460 --> 00:21:26.430
Inarizaki                                                                                                        Karasuno

327
00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:26.430
Karasuno somehow manages to stop 
Inarizaki from getting a break point!

328
00:21:26.430 --> 00:21:30.640
Wow, I'm sure Hinata-kun messes 
around with the ball all the time.

329
00:21:30.640 --> 00:21:33.890
Damn it! Don't get exhausted now!

330
00:21:34.930 --> 00:21:39.560
I know you didn't mean anything by it.
 Sorry for going on that rant.

331
00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:44.840
No, uh... I think it'd be worse 
if I said that without thinking.

332
00:21:45.780 --> 00:21:48.280
Damn it, my brain is gonna be sore tonight.

333
00:21:53.060 --> 00:21:54.290
Complain, damn it!

334
00:21:54.290 --> 00:21:56.040
Complain? Why?

335
00:21:57.990 --> 00:21:59.210
Gimme the next one, too!

336
00:22:02.400 --> 00:22:06.940
I thought Kageyama had nothing 
to be scared of anymore.

337
00:22:06.940 --> 00:22:07.800
But...

338
00:22:08.530 --> 00:22:13.310
It's not just the enemy that can 
push you beyond your limits.

339
00:22:17.170 --> 00:22:21.420
I'm moved, Shoyo-kun.

340
00:23:51.990 --> 00:23:56.990
Episode 24: Monsters' Ball

341
00:23:53.280 --> 00:23:56.420
Next time, "Monsters' Ball."
